reviews.review_text: Awesome selections of budget friendly organic meats and spices. We have been coming here for over 10yrs and always stock up on meats. They recently started to have chicken bones and pork bones for 2-8$ range and its great for making soups in winter!

Love, love, love this place. Been a customer here for over 30 years. They carry some of the best organic meats and produce. Their selection of grains, spices and snacks are commendable. Never disappointed.

Famous Foods is THE BEST FOOD STORE EVER. Organic bulk everything, foods from Europe and South America, grass-fed meats, 20 different kinds of honey...It is a treasure trove. I could easily spend half my day and all my money there.
Famous foods is a Vancouver health food store staple. Their butcher is amazing. Best quality steaks at the best prices in Vancouver. Located on Kingsway.
The best grocery store in the neighborhood. Has an incredible selection of organic and natural foods and products, great bulk products, and very reasonable prices! Absolutely love this place.

I love this place. Its my go to place for grass fed steaks and beef. They have a variety of ethnic foods and seasonings. If youre looking for something specific that other grocery stores may not have, this is the place to go to.

Gengar sweatshirt cashier you rock! Also long hair beard guy in the spice section helping me when cross eyed looking at 50 spices. And cheese section sweatshirt elevator operator gal you are also awesome!
Looked for my vegan Thanksgiving dinner high and low...eventually found it at Famous Foods. Fantastic variety of international food, including Irn Bru from Glasgow, Scotland.
I love Famous Foods. Cheap meats & vegan things. Ability to feel healthy while you re just in there. So cool.

Not as big as choices, capers, whole foods, etc. But they still have fancy high end groceries, and whenever they have an item on sale, the discount is actually quite large. Most importantly is the cheese section. It isnt uncommon to see them at like 50% off, while you are there, scooch over to the left and look for reduced meat. High end gourmet grocery stores dont have to be overpriced all the time. If you are in the area, check it out, you might get lucky and buy something fancy at a regular price!

I am not sure what happened to my review, I was almost sure I left one, because of all the places I could review locally, this is one of the places I would like to most highly review, largely due to how much I appreciate their various offerings and prices/deals, especially on meats, which has helped me to make better food choices and experience improvements in my health. Thank you for all you do to bless this community. God bless you Famous Foods, thank you for all the great deals and the hard work and kind service from your team.
Love the selection of goods here. One of the few places to buy bulk spices. And at much better value than the big grocery stores.
VERY GREAT AND GOOD GROCERY STORE AND LOTS OF SELECTION. STAFF ARE GREAT AND FRIENDLY.
Great prices and excellent customer service! This store makes grocery shopping a pleasant experience every time.

Best selection of organic meat. Great prices on protein. Produce section is small however. Stick to meat and bulk items. Coffee. Great selection of non alcoholic beverages. The best peanut butter Ive ever had.

The best grocery store in Vancouver! Just feels like I am not lining the pockets of another Billionaire grocery store owner. Excellent bulk products with a focus throughout the store of organic and natural.
Knowledgeable staff was very impressive. My go to store for bulk food. I buy soy beans to make miso paste.
Great , local grocery store. Awesome selection! I come here for their huge bulk foods selection. They have a ton of products that I cannot find elsewhere. Bonus? Great staff and free parking!
Love the vegan options and selection of pastas. Also, pre made bags of bulk goods with lots of organic options

Famous Foods is one of my favourite grocery stores ever. It s been around a long time and if anything it keeps getting better. Service is super helpful and genuinely friendly and caring. I know this is just a grocery store but when it comes to products and prices they really are worth checking out.
Cheapest food price Ive seen in all Vancouver and the quality is still very good.
If youre looking for an unusual ingredient for your baking or cooking, youll likely find it here. Plus lots of organic products.
Great assortment of products. Friendly staff, locally owned.

Still the best place for goats milk dairy products and gluten free products, non-sulfured, unsweetened dried fruits, for organic meats, for bulk seeds and spices, and really good coffee. If you have food allergies of any kind, this place should be on your list of go-to places. I moved from East Van to Burnaby, to Surrey ....and for more than thirty years, Famous Foods has been my go-to for all my special food needs. Did I mention that their organic meats are really good. ...well, they are.

I love this place. Their stock/selection is stellar. Their selection of flours, dried beans, dried fruits, granolas, veggie microwave meals, and so much more is just wonderful. Their hours are good too! The staff are super helpful and friendly. Just a great place to shop overall.

Famous foods is hands down the best little grocery store in Vancouver. And I say little bit it has everything you needs, has a bigger range of specialty goods (organic, gluten free, minimal packaging) then a lot of the bigger and more expensive stores. It s quick to get in and do a shop and leave without feeling overwhelmed. Can t say enough good things about this place. Family favourite through and through.

Excellent local grocery store for organic and tough to find baking / cooking ingredients. There s some ingredients there that I haven t found in any other store. Their bulk section is great! I love the variety of flours, dried foods and specialty items that inspire me to cook more creatively!

What a wonderful selection of baking ingredients they have!! The big chains didnt carry Coconut Extract AND had much less options for coconut oil. I got everything I needed to make coconut lime cupcakes

This is an amazing store for the gourmet cook. They have great spices and other hard to find foods. And for a baker this store has a wide selection of organic flours and other baking supplies. The only downside is that it can be quite busy depending on the time and day that you go. They also have really good customer service so feel free to ask for help

This place continues to amaze me. From natural pork sausages and bacon, Jersey butter, wild prawns from Argentina, non-diary ice cream from Say Hello Sweets to multiple brands of Oxygen bleach, they have it all. I will only buy organic chicken breast from them   for some reason, organic chicken breast from other organic stores are tough by comparison. Their staff is friendly and helpful. They are happy to bring goods in for me. I love the packaged bulk goods as well. They are truly small enough to know you, and their selection is healthy and wide enough to be my go-to grocery store.

One stop shopping place. It is a great local option for variety of bulk, natural and general groceries. Rare finds that cant be found on bulk at other markets. Best accessed by car but limited parking. The store can get busy quite quickly.
Absolute favorite place to get organic meats. Great prices, selection and service. A gem that I hope never gives in to the large corporations and their terrible take on groceries.

Easy to see why they are famous! Love this place from the bottom of my heart. $33 for 25kg of beans, thats 85000 calories folks. Not to mention they have vegan savory pies in the deli, and they helped me to my car! 6/5 best grocery store in Vancouver.

Superb local grocery store.  Lots of options, gluten free, organic, vegan, you name it they probably have it!  Bulk style section for dry goods, baking supplies and spices. We ordered home delivery today and the service and drop off was impeccable!  Produce is so fresh and they had all organic meat options.  Thank you!

This place is excellent all round and an appreciated community staple to many. Famous foods promotes supporting local, fresh, organic ingredients and they will go out of their way to accommodate finding specific items on your wish list. It always surprises me when people come down on places we actually need more of for things that are completely out of their control. Like a fridge suddenly breaking down and them having to discard of the cheese for the safety of the public but its now an inconvenience because they never anticipated that or warned said shopper that they didnt have a back up fridge laying around or that 80 years ago they never anticipated a global pandemic and didnt put the proper social distancing measures in place by doubling the isle size so shopper with their newborn could feel safer. They try their best and they succeed at it. We are lucky to have Famous Foods, the staff they employee and the farmers/farms they work with.

Selection and prices are awesome in this place! Now my favorite goto when Im in the area! Was so disappointed by Los Guerreros Mexican Food Products that this shop made my day! And allowed me to make my horchata haha And friendly service that spoke English... outstanding!

Famous Foods is excellent, from organic peanut butter and local honey to whole organic spices and organic fruit. I go there when I want to stock up specifically on quality, affordable pantry staples such as flour, spices, nuts, and seeds. The emphasis is on quality rather than flashy packaging and there is a minimum of corporate branded or processed, packaged foods. The aisles have a large amount of Famous Foods unbranded, portioned ingredients. The quality of these items is superb and the value for money is a very sweet ratio. Always recommended.

Great selection of foods like flours or other items usually found in bulk. I was able to find all that I needed and a bit more. Great selection, friendly people. The variety of items is very good. Employees are very helpful and friendly.

Famous foods is a really fun place to go. Now you may be thinking why is a grocery store fun to go to? Well! Famous foods has tons of fun things that you dont usually see, such as like 15 different types of flour to make bread or dehydrated hummus. Its just a fun and cool place to go to.

You can find fresh produce and organic meats. Lots of bulk foods at a fraction  of  cost compared to branded items. Very convenient and staff is helpful when I wanted to get brewers yeast. And you will find quite a few items on sale but instore that you wont see in the flyers

What a great store! The prices for bulk goods is quite reasonable, and the selection is vast. Its  nice having the choice to keep my containers filled without having to purchase more than what I need...or having all the excess packaging. All their products are fresh, and the shelves are kept filled. Ive found the staff, to always be polite and helpful.  The store is kept really clean, and the aisles are swept, and kept free of carts and boxes. It has been alot busier as of late, and the parking lot in the back is often full.  There is street parking also available, however during the rush hour that parking is non existent. The store is definitely worth the visit, and dont forget your reusable bags.
Awesome shop for hard to find grocery items. They also carry a full range of regular groceries. Amazing selection of herbs and spices, baking ingredients, and fresh food.

Amazing gem of a grocery store. Current restrictions for covid safety mean waiting in a line sometimes but the experience shopping is so worth it, this is the safest I have felt shopping since March. There are a variety of options for vegan, organic, and local for most products.

Famous Foods provides exceptional customer service. I was looking for a particular brand of flour and called to inquire to see if it was possible to get at Famous Foods. Cam went above and beyond to find and order the product for me. I can not say enough good things about Famous Foods! Fantastic local company!

One of my favorite stops for specialty items. When you enter in through the doors the exotic smells of spices  permeates the air, love it. I purchase much of our families meat here, always fresh and priced well. Dried goods also a go to for us. I usually pass on buying produce here, not their forte. Very East Van, my hood. Cheers

The staff are always helpful and I can always find ingredients not normally sourced in larger grocery stores. They have an amazing collection of herbs and spices, and their flour has yielded my best baking results.

The store has been at this location for over 30 years. It has a bit of everything but the things that stand out for me are the dry goods isles and the small meat selection. Good mixture of organics vs standard items throughout. Lots of locally sourced products.

Fantastic produce, exceptional spices and herbs selection and price, friendly staff. The bonus point us for stocking the entire Avalon dairy range, as well as one of the few places that sells sour cream with just 2 ingredients, milk and cultures. Absolutely recommend and will continue being a regular customer.

A culinary paradise! They have lots of ingredients you wont be able to find anywhere else! Their spice/herb section has me stuck for a good 10-15 minutes. The meat is fresh, they have a small produce section which is perfect for a quick grocery run and they carry many local products! A must visit if youre interested in cooking...and eating    .
Love their meat department. Many choices of organic meats. Especially like their grass fed beef. They often have meat products on sale. Quality meat at bargain prices - hard to get elsewhere.

I bought Organic wheat bran a year ago.its finished with no changes or ruined. They pack and sell freshly and clean. I never buy meat here because I need halal hand slaughtered. Many nice people working inside , ready to help . Big thumbs up and 5
famous foods always has a nice ambiance. its a bit niche but its always reliable if you want something thats hard to find!

A Vancouver landmark since circa 1968? best place to find dried herbs and odd spices, top quality in dried fruits and nuts, seeds and grains. baking supplies etc. what a good grocery store should be. Every foodie should visit here just once, you will return. General Store? Grocery Store? Neighborhood Food Store?

Good selection of baking supplies, some organic. Other specialty items, brands you might not see elsewhere, some organic. Some organic produce. Not wheelchair accessible,  but if you are frail or walk with a cane, they will help you carry your bags to your car.

What a great store. Lots of organics, alternative choices if you are gluten-free, bulk foods already portioned to useable sizes (beans, rice, dried veggies, fruits, baking supplies, grains, flours...) Super choices of teas, coffees, jams, soups, spices, olive oils, seasonings, pastas, chips. Complete dairy section with non dairy choices available too. Good supplies in the vitamin and skin care area. My go to store for buying all my supplies for gluten free baking for Christmas, Easter and all holidays. I like their meat section as they have lots of organic, local grass fed. Plan to spend a good amount of time in their store as the choices and selections are amazing. Check out their organic crunchy peanut butter!

This is easily my favorite grocery store. Everything is in minimal packaging & almost all of it is natural & organic. You can find all kinds of fun new things here like birch water, effervescent, 5 mushroom tea... They also have a wide range of dried herbs & natural soaps & cleansers for any DIY projects you may have (edible or otherwise). I highly recommend having a look if you havent already.

They are a nice little store great for natural and organic source foods. Found things here that are difficult to find in the valley. Worth the drive? Possibly, if you cant find what youre looking for elsewhere. If youre local, great place to shop. Customer service is outstanding.

Famous Foods is a classic in this city, offering not only standard grocery items, but also specialzing is bulk buying at bargain basement prices! They definitely carry some non run-of-the-mill oddities, but its always a delight and a pleasant surprise to come across something that you couldnt find elsewhere! Great place to shop with parking available too!

Easily my favourite grocery store in Vancouver, my only wish is that it was closer to home! Huge range of products, including a ton of rare and hard to find specialty products. Great butchers department, and a small but lovely deli. Everything is well priced, and its well worth the visit.

One of Vancouvers best longstanding businesses. Huge variety of things you wont be able to find in your chain supermarkets and mostly affordable since they buy in bulk and repackage. Good place to shop for baking supplies, dried chiles, and beans. Produce is variable. Staff are always very nice and knowledgeable. The meat is very high quality and worth the money. Parking can be a bit of a zoo on weekends, so plan accordingly.

Independent grocery with a very friendly staff. Been shopping here for years. Has stuff you can t get anywhere else. Lots of pre-packaged bulk goods. Lots of earth friendly choices. Excellent produce.
Famous Foods is one of my fave grocery stores! Awesome selection of health and bulk foods. I like buying non-medicated chicken here. Its super tasty - especially their wings.
Shelves are stocked well.  Prices are usually fair.  Watch for their weekly flyer that starts every Thursday.

I love this place. Ive been going there since the 70s or 80s. Ever since they opened. I used to live nearby but now its a 20 minute drive but certainly worth it. Cool funky store with stuff you wont find anywhere else. Nice variety of bread and other stuff.

Love coming here to buy groceries.  They have a great selection of dry ingredients and spices you wouldnt be able to find at a typical grocery store. Most of the meats are organic, grass fed or non medicated at half the price of stores like whole foods. Only thing is seafood wise they dont have too many options. They also do not use styrofoam to package their meat which I really appreciate.

I have been shopping at this  store door over. 20 years. If you want some item from another country or just good, organic items, this is the place.  Some things have had to change due to present conditions. There are no bulk items and I cant get large containers of honey now, but the same family runs it with their helpful manner. Want something they dont have? Ask them if they will order it for you.

Love this place! Great healthy and organic grocery options. The deli is good the meat is good the produce is good. The bulk food section is the best. Im amazed at the options they can fit in such a small space. Staff are also excellent and helpful.

This is the best place in east van for organic and grass fed meats. Their meats are usually even cheaper than non organic stuff you get at other stores. They also have a large bulk section with lots of organic options. Great selection of olive oils and other italianish specialty foods. Always worth the extra trip when your shopping for the weeks groceries.

One of my favourite places to buy groceries. Most things here are the best prices Ive seen anywhere, especially for things like organic honey and peanut butter. There is a great variety of beans, flours, and spices in the bulk section; with a good selection of organic meats too.

Great variety of foods from all over the world. Good quality of the products. Beef was on sale, got a good deal. Customer rep guy on the phone is not the friendliest, but the experience in store makes it up.

This is the place to go for quality dried foods. Bulk products are pre packaged so less worry about cross contamination and age than bulk bins. Theyre also great at making up custom packages if you want more than their typical quantities. Ordering in products that are hard to find is sometimes an option too, even if they may not usually carry them. Produce and perishables are a bit more expensive so I usually go elsewhere for those.

Excellent place to get Organic Food, the best Organic Food in Vancouver, Canada  . The service is awsome and all the people who work in the Supermarket are very friendly and super easygoing. I love the place, the food is Organic and Natural so it is healthy and highly recommended for everyone!

Everything is fresh, staff are always friendly and will always help you find something if you need. Vast range of herbs, spices lentils, grains etc. Ive started to eat healthier since ive been shopping here. Its a pleasure to buy my weekly groceries and I really enjoy the experience as I always find what I need. Being an avid baker and cook at home, this is important. Unlike Safeway or Save on where finding a fresh tomato is like trying to find gold on the moon. Prices may be higher but its worth it. Their points system is excellent and you can usually get a good deal in their meat section. Highly recommended!
Great place to find organic and allergen free foods. They carry products that I cant find elsewhere. Decent prices. I come here to buy non medicated chicken parts to make bone broth.

A great store full of specialized products that work with my allergies and gluten free needs. Nice selection of cheeses, meats, dried foods, flours, baking supplies (raisins, nuts, dates...). My go to store for holiday treats.

Great selection of pantry items packed in pound to half-pound sizes. Also a variety of spices in smaller packaging great for refilling spice jars. Todays shop meant I picked up tomato powder, ground almonds, dried non-crystallized (and crystallized) ginger, whole yellow mustard seeds as well as small packets of xanthan gum. They also have a nice fresh organic produce section and carry local dairy products (Dairyland and Avalon). Aisles are clearly marked and the store was very clean. I liked that they had a lot of good quality non-fragranced cleaning products that didnt have isothiazolinones (a group of preservatives Im allergic to). High quality items in an unpretentious setting.

Had such a great shopping experience there. The staff were so helpful, shout out to Santiago who was so knowledgable and really took the time to talk to us about all things flour! We ended up getting quite a bit And trying it out. Look forward to returning soon!

I just called in and asked if they have champagne yeast, unfortunately they didn t have it but the gentleman on the phone did a quick search and found out where I can get them! It was very helpful he did that for me as I had no idea where to even start! Thank you, I am happy there is a store like that fully supports local business :)

I love this grocery shop, its like how things used to be.  The meat is fantastic and theres always good deals to be had there.  They have a good selection of all types of foods and the spice section is great.

One of my favorite places to shop.  They carry a good range of ethically sourced and organic food along with a lot of harder to find specialty products and bulk items you wont find at your typical grocery store.
Love their bar soap from The Soap Works natural Bee   pollen, oat meal, shampoo and conditioner. Organic Food Store at its finest

Great place to find specialty items like freeze dried veggies & meal mixes for camping, or imported cheeses like Ski Queen, or small amounts of hard to find bulk items like xanthan gum or citric acid or nutritional yeast. Always friendly staff & good bike parking right outside the doors.

Absolutely best grocery store in great Van. I highly recommend it for being fully stocked on almost everything I want. This especially includes my lactose intolerance. They care about being environmentally friendly by reducing packaging.

Awesome store! They have a lot of cheap items that they buy in bulk and then package themselves. For example dried beans, spices, oats, nuts, and seeds. They have nutritional yeast in large quantities for reasonable prices which is often very hard to find.

This place has everything, if youre after cheap groceries then this might not be the best place to shop but if youre looking for something in particular or if youre trying to eat more consciously then this is a great place to shop. The store has been around for ages but I still feel like its a hidden gem, maybe cause its hidden Im the east side??? Any who everytime Ive been in the place has never been full and the isles are nice and wide so it doesnt feel cramped. As Ive mentioned before this place has everything, Im talking every herb you can think of and some youve probably never even knew existed. Also if youre keen on making your own food such as yogurt, cheese, or beer then theyve got the stuff to help you along. As youve probably figured out by now the store caters to those who are after organic food so it was also nice to see meats as well that were non medicated as well as organic.
Vancouvers Organic Food  hub. Lots of different varieties at good prices.

Today at about 1730 I popped in looking for Nori sheets .. couldnt find them..so I asked the young kid ( blond wearing a white cloth mask) for his help. He stopped right away stocking the shelf and went in search of what I needed! I couldnt catch his name -but I wanted to recognize him for one of the best costumer service experiences Ive ever had. He is one of the reasons I love Famous Foods! Im so sorry I didnt catch your name and called you a Blondie! You are The Best!! Thank you!

In this moment of uncertainty  and compromised access, Famous Foods is a beacon of quality goods, ethically sourced products and AMAZING CUSTOMER SERVICE!!!!  Thanks for helping me out with an order, Cam you and your staff have gone beyond any expectations I might have had.  I am so GRATEFUL for your store!

Its amazing how they can fit so many SKUs in such a small retail space. This is the place to come if you are looking for obscure ingredients for that obscure recipe youve been saving. Bulk items are all conveniently prepacked into various sizes of plastic bags. Deli has a nice selection of ready-to-go lunch food.
This a really old school healthy food store, staff are all friendly and helpful, still helpful as ever.  Still the greatest
Always a pleasant shopping trip.

Great prices, very good selection, all necessary things, fruits could be slightly better not commercially produced from USA. Selection of honey could be improved. Otherwise you ll find almost everything you want. Definitely my favourite shop in Vancouver

Best place in the city for BULK items. Also one of the last places to easily buy dried GUAVA in the city. They also have Lexia raisins and Muscat raisins -- also hard to find. The store has a town feel to it and they seem to be pretty strict with is deemed to be Organic And they stick to it. There is a bakery, spices isle, bulk isle, frozen foods, fruits, veggies. chocolate, baking needs, juices, extracts and flavorings. Parking is not that great, but they do have a small lot.

A great local grocer. This place has been here for generations. Me and my mom both love this place for their most speciality items. Where the fresh produce can be lacking sometimes they make up for with imported goods. Delicious deli selections, and delicatessen items. A seriously Kingsway staple! Long live famous foods.

This is one of my family s favourite go-to stores for quality natural foods especially various whole-grain flours and other baking products. They also have a very wide selection of fruits, produce, dairy, meat and canned foods (Special feature: they package many products onsite.)

Ive been shopping at Famous since they opened in 1995. I couldnt believe how good the prices were compared to Choices and Capers, and an awesome selection of organic meats and other foods (grains). Best organic popcorn you can get.
One of my favorite independent grocers around Vancouver. Good deals, great bulk (prepackaged) selection, and lots of organic selection. Owner is very accommodating and puts customers first.

Some of the best savings and varieties of organic options! A must go place for all diets for the essentials. Love this place. Glad my friend who owns The Tipper Restaurant introduced this place to me!

Great market for people who like to cook. The selection here is amazing! I really liked that most of the foods is bulk style, and that they dont carry any of the so-called food that is rampant these days. good selection of organic produce as well! Great market for people who like to cook

Great place for  those who care about healthy options and the environment. Bulk selection is good and produce is fresh. Tight space for those of us who do not live in Vancouver but very worthwhile the visit.
